1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,929
It holds true not only on the golf course, but in every facet of life.

2
00:00:07,120 --> 00:00:11,010
Four things you can do to lick health excusitis.

3
00:00:11,120 --> 00:00:16,370
The best vaccine against health excusitis consists of these four doses.

4
00:00:16,370 --> 00:00:17,650
1.

5
00:00:18,080 --> 00:00:20,370
Refuse to talk about your health.

6
00:00:20,560 --> 00:00:25,970
The more you talk about an ailment, even the common cold, the worse it seems to get.

7
00:00:26,320 --> 00:00:30,610
Talking about bad health is like putting fertilizer on weeds.

8
00:00:30,880 --> 00:00:34,210
Besides, talking about your health is a bad habit.

9
00:00:34,240 --> 00:00:35,569
It bores people.

10
00:00:35,680 --> 00:00:39,010
It makes one appear self-centered and old maidish.

11
00:00:39,280 --> 00:00:44,689
Success-minded people defeat the natural tendency to talk about their bad health.

12
00:00:45,120 --> 00:00:50,530
One may, and let me emphasize the word may, get a little sympathy,

13
00:00:50,640 --> 00:00:55,410
but one doesn't get respect and loyalty by being a chronic complainer.

14
00:00:55,410 --> 00:00:56,929
2.

15
00:00:57,200 --> 00:00:59,569
Refuse to worry about your health.

16
00:00:59,840 --> 00:01:06,289
Dr. Walter Alvarez, emeritus consultant to the world-famous Mayo Clinic, wrote recently,

17
00:01:06,720 --> 00:01:10,929
I always beg worriers to exercise some self-control.

18
00:01:11,040 --> 00:01:16,929
For instance, when I saw this man, a fellow who was convinced he had a diseased gallbladder,

19
00:01:16,929 --> 00:01:22,610
although eight separate x-ray examinations showed that the organ was perfectly normal,

20
00:01:22,880 --> 00:01:26,530
I begged him to quit getting his gallbladder x-rayed.

21
00:01:26,880 --> 00:01:32,850
I have begged hundreds of heart-conscious men to quit getting electrocardiograms made.

22
00:01:32,850 --> 00:01:34,689
3.

23
00:01:35,120 --> 00:01:39,250
Be genuinely grateful that your health is as good as it is.

24
00:01:39,520 --> 00:01:42,289
There's an old saying worth repeating often.

25
00:01:42,560 --> 00:01:48,770
I felt sorry for myself because I had ragged shoes until I met a man who had no feet.

26
00:01:49,280 --> 00:01:55,730
Instead of complaining about not feeling good, it's far better to be glad you are as healthy as you are.

27
00:01:56,080 --> 00:02:04,929
Just being grateful for the health you have is powerful vaccination against developing new aches and pains and real illness.

28
00:02:05,040 --> 00:02:06,689
4.

29
00:02:06,960 --> 00:02:11,730
Remind yourself often, it's better to wear out than rust out.

30
00:02:12,160 --> 00:02:14,130
Life is yours to enjoy.

31
00:02:14,240 --> 00:02:15,330
Don't waste it.

32
00:02:15,520 --> 00:02:19,970
Don't pass up living by thinking yourself into a hospital bed.

